<subSubSection id="CAA594639598A73F54639DBB8FB4AB29" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph id="5ED7E5130B52AE1ED317DB4D00E5C3B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2DACA72EE2CB3C24EFD9A85D75DBE62" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The above single female specimen is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EB542C3D200B1B8293D52215A48BFD80" family="Staphylinidae" genus="B." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="B. proximus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="proximus">
<emphasis id="57197D90E34F5EB95B6B37892F5CC8D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. proximus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but could also represent an undescribed species. The genus is newly reported from the island of Sumatra, where it is undoubtedly diverse but extremely poorly sampled.
</paragraph>
